message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Nauru in the past 5 years was the signing of the Regional Processing Agreement (RPA) between Nauru and Australia in 2013. Under this agreement, Nauru became one of the offshore processing centers for asylum seekers attempting to reach Australia by boat. This agreement had a significant impact on Nauru's economy and social fabric, as the country experienced an influx of asylum seekers and the establishment of detention centers. The RPA has been a subject of controversy and criticism, with concerns raised about the treatment of asylum seekers and their living conditions on the island.
